%N A393690 Decimal expansion of lim_{x->oo} Sum_{p<=x} log(p)^2/p - log(x)^2/2 (negated).
%H A393690 Artur Kawalec, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.21535">On the series expansion of the prime zeta function about s = 1 and its coefficients</a>, arXiv:2603.21535 [math.NT], 2026, p. 3 eq. 15 and 17.
%F A393690 Equals gamma^2 + 2*gamma1 - Sum_{n>=2} mu(n)*n*(-Zeta'(n)^2/Zeta(n)^2 + Zeta''(n)/Zeta(n)), where gamma1 is StieltjesGamma(1).
%F A393690 Equals -Integral_{x>=1} (pi(x) - li(x))*(log(x)^2 - 2*log(x))/x^2 dx.
%F A393690 Equals: -2 * 2-th coefficient of expansion of the function P(x)-log(x-1) at x=1, where P(x) is Prime zeta function (coefficient by (x-1)^2).
%F A393690 Equals: -2 * 2-th coefficient of expansion of the function P(1+1/x)-log(x) at x=Infinity, where P(x) is Prime zeta function (coefficient by 1/x^2).
%F A393690 Equals A155969 - A346832 + A394622.
%e A393690 2.555107615446445239595583797989464445...
%t A393690 N[EulerGamma^2 + 2*StieltjesGamma[1] - Sum[MoebiusMu[k]*k*(-Zeta'[k]^2/Zeta[k]^2 + Zeta''[k]/Zeta[k]), {k, 2, 1000}], 110] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_ *)
